ised everyone by first-ever French category-based <a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/express-entry\/\"><strong>Express Entry<\/strong><\/a> draw, inviting 2,300 candidates who possess strong French-speaking skills. The minimum Comprehensive Ranking System (CRS) score required for this draw was 439, marking the lowest CRS score of the year 2023.<\/p>\n<p>The latest Express Entry draw marks the sixth round of invitations issued within a span of two weeks, bringing the total number of candidates invited through the Express Entry system during this period to <strong>9,800<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>The majority of invitations were issued this week. The most recent draw, which occurred on <a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/news\/canada-targeted-express-entry-draw-healthcare-july-6-2023\/\"><strong>July 6<\/strong><\/a>, invited <strong>1,500 candidates<\/strong> with work experience in healthcare fields. This draw was expected after an announcement was made alongside the first-ever Express Entry invitations extended to <strong>500<\/strong> healthcare professionals on <a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/news\/canada-targeted-express-entry-draw-june-2023-healthcare\/\"><strong>June 27<\/strong><\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>On <a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/news\/category-based-express-entry-draw-for-stem-category\/\"><strong>July 5<\/strong><\/a>, another notable draw was held, specifically targeting candidates in science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) professions. In this round, <strong>500 candidates<\/strong> were invited, and the minimum CRS score required was <strong>486<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<h3>Targeted Express Entry Draw July 7, 2023 Results:<\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Express Entry Round:<\/strong> #256<\/li>\n<li><strong>Draw Type:<\/strong> Category-Based Targeted<\/li>\n<li><strong>Draw Date:<\/strong> July 7, 2023<\/li>\n<li><strong>CRS Cut-off Score:<\/strong> 439<\/li>\n<li><strong>No. of invitations:<\/strong> 2,300<\/li>\n<li><strong>Tie-breaking rule:<\/strong> January 20, 2023<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner equal_height=&#8221;yes&#8221; content_placement=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221;][vc_column_inner column_padding=&#8221;padding-6-percent&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; centered_text=&#8221;true&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221;][nectar_btn size=&#8221;large&#8221; button_style=&#8221;regular&#8221; button_color_2=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; icon_family=&#8221;default_arrow&#8221; text=&#8221;Start Express Entry Assessment Now&#8221; url=&#8221;https:\/\/bit.ly\/start-free-assessment&#8221;][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][vc_column_text]\n<h2>Targeted Express Entry for Francophone Immigrants<\/h2>\n<p>The only category-based selection criteria that don&#8217;t rely on work experience is strong is the <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/canada-targeted-express-entry\/french-speakers\/\">Targeted Express Entry for French-speaking immigrants<\/a><\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>Canada&#8217;s immigration minister has the goal of promoting the <strong>French language<\/strong> outside of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/quebec-immigration\/\"><strong>Quebec<\/strong><\/a>. By prioritizing the invitation of French-speaking newcomers, Canada aims to support economic growth through Francophone immigration in regions outside Quebec. This approach recognizes the valuable contribution and the strengthening effect that French-speaking communities bring to these areas.<\/p>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner equal_height=&#8221;yes&#8221; content_placement=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; top_padding=&#8221;5%&#8221; bottom_padding=&#8221;5%&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221;][vc_column_inner column_padding=&#8221;no-extra-padding&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color=&#8221;#96001c&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221;][image_with_animation image_url=&#8221;10674&#8243; animation=&#8221;Fade In From Bottom&#8221; hover_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; alignment=&#8221;&#8221; border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; box_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; image_loading=&#8221;default&#8221; max_width=&#8221;100%&#8221; max_width_mobile=&#8221;default&#8221;][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner column_padding=&#8221;padding-6-percent&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_elem